# Project Structure

This is a Ruby on Rails 8.0 application with a modern frontend setup using Vite, Stimulus, and ViewComponent.

## Main Directories

- [app](mdc:app): Contains the MVC components (models, views, controllers) and frontend code
- [config](mdc:config): Contains configuration for routes, database, environments, etc.
- [db](mdc:db): Contains database migrations and schema
- [lib](mdc:lib): Contains utility code and custom tasks
- [spec](mdc:spec): Contains RSpec tests

## Key Files

- [Gemfile](mdc:Gemfile): Ruby dependencies
- [package.json](mdc:package.json): JavaScript dependencies
- [config/routes.rb](mdc:config/routes.rb): Application routes
- [vite.config.ts](mdc:vite.config.ts): Vite configuration for frontend assets
- [config/application.rb](mdc:config/application.rb): Main application configuration

## Key Directives
- use the Rails MCP tooling whenever possible.
